This paper discusses the use of Sequence-to-Sequence Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs) in language learning and generalization, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a new environment for testing the RNNs, which involves logical expressions and complex commands, indicating a potential connection to artificial intelligence (AI) and neural networks (NE). Finally, the paper also proposes a data augmentation method, which could potentially involve computer vision (CV) techniques.
